  </head>
  <body>
    <g:set var="navTitle" value="Instructions" scope="request"/>
    <div class="helpbody">
      <table class="helptable">
        <tr>
          <td class="helpentry">1.  Select your station out of list of stations.</td>
          <td class="hellpentry">(Picture goes here)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>(Picture goes here)</td>
          <td>
            <p>2. Select whether you want to update or make a new post to your station.</p>
            <p>If updating, go to step 3.  If making a new post, go to step 4.</p>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>
            <p>3. Edit the corresponding values you wish to change, and press submit.</p>
            <p>This can include adding pictures, changing your comment, or your position.</p>
            <p>Once completed, you will return to the view in step 2.</p>
          </td>
          <td>(Picture goes here)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>(Picture goes here)</td>
          <td>
            <p>4. Add the photos of the rain gauge</p>
            <p>Your photos should include:</p>
            <ol>
              <li>A photo of the rain gauge.</li>
              <li>A photo of the sky above the rain gauge.</li>
              <li>A photo of the area north of the rain gauge.</li>
              <li>A photo of the area south of the rain gauge.</li>
              <li>A photo of the area east of the rain gauge.</li>
              <li>A photo of the area west of the rain gauge.</li>
            </ol>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>
            <p>5. Add any comments you'd like about the post.</p>
            <p>If you'd like to keep your post private, click the "private" check-box.</p>
          </td>
          <td>(Picture goes here)</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </body>
